    <h1>Coron&#xAD;avirus curbs</h1>
    <h2>A look at the mea&#xAD;sures in var&#xAD;i&#xAD;ous coun&#xAD;tries in Europe.</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210110/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-10"><time>2021-01-10</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Norway</p>
    <p>• Ban on serv­ing al­co­hol in restau­rants and bars from Jan 4 to Jan 18 • Manda­tory Covid-19 tests for all people en­ter­ing Norway from abroad, ei­ther upon ar­rival or within 24 hours The Nether­lands</p>
    <p>• Non-es­sen­tial shops and busi­nesses, gyms, mu­se­ums, cin­e­mas and the­atres shut un­til at least Jan 19 from Dec 15</p>
    <p>• The Dutch are ad­vised to stay at home and may have only a max­i­mum of two guests a day Bri­tain</p>
    <p>• Since Jan 5, pri­mary and sec­ondary schools and col­leges re­main closed at least un­til mid-Fe­bru­ary for face-to-face learn­ing ex­cept to the chil­dren of key work­ers and vul­ner­a­ble pupils • Em­ploy­ees to work from home if they can, and leave home only for es­sen­tial trips Spain</p>
    <p>• Re­gional re­stric­tions in place • For ex­am­ple, be­tween Jan 7 and Jan 17, Cat­alo­ni­ans are barred from leav­ing their mu­nic­i­pal­ity; gyms and shop­ping cen­tres must close Swe­den</p>
    <p>• Mu­nic­i­pal­ity gyms, pools and li­braries to close un­til Jan 24 • New law aimed at mak­ing it eas­ier for the govern­ment to im­pose fur­ther re­stric­tions comes into force to­day France</p>
    <p>• 8pm to 6am cur­few in var­i­ous parts of France since Dec 15</p>
    <p>• Restau­rants, bars, night­clubs, and public places such as cin­e­mas and the­atres closed Ger­many</p>
    <p>• Lock­down, which started on Nov 2 and sup­posed to end to­day, is ex­tended un­til Jan 31</p>
    <p>• Limit on gath­er­ings, with mem­bers of any one house­hold be­ing al­lowed to meet only one other per­son Poland</p>
    <p>• Public gath­er­ings limited to five people</p>
    <p>• Three-week strict lock­down be­tween Dec 28 and Jan 17, and all ar­rivals from abroad re­quired to iso­late for 10 days Hun­gary</p>
    <p>• Shops re­main open but the coun­try ’s bor­ders are closed to al­most all vis­i­tors, in­clud­ing cit­i­zens of other Euro­pean Union na­tions</p>
    <p>• Cur­few be­tween 8pm and 5am since Novem­ber, set to ex­pire on Feb 1 Italy</p>
    <p>• Travel pro­hib­ited be­tween the coun­try ’s re­gions ex­cept for health or work rea­sons at least un­til Jan 15 from Dec 21</p>
    <p>• People who live in ar­eas hit the hard­est by Covid-19 per­mit­ted to “move” just once a day to another sin­gle pri­vate home in their mu­nic­i­pal­ity TEXT: AW CHENG WEI SUN­DAY TIMES GRAPH­ICS</p>

